Package: xtop
Version: 0.47.11-1
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: libc6
Recommends: postgresql, journalctl
Installed-Size: 38440
Maintainer: Farhan Tahir <farhan.003@gmail.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/ftahirops/xtop
Description: Incident-first root-cause analysis console for Linux
 v0.47.11 ships full ClickHouse integration plus a long list of
 UI and RCA correctness fixes captured during a live VM session.
 .
 ClickHouse:
   - New collector/apps/mod_clickhouse.go: detection by PID + port,
     dedup across multiple listeners, optional clickhouse-client
     subprocess query backed by /root/.xtop_secrets credentials.
   - 18 deep metrics: queries, mutations, merges, replication
     queue, replicas degraded, databases, active parts, total
     rows, top tables, top queries (1h), errors (5min), top
     error, mark / uncompressed cache hit %, async-insert queue,
     and per-tick recommendations.
   - New UI renderer (ui/page_apps_clickhouse.go) groups deep
     metrics into Health / Storage / Queries / Ingest / Caches /
     Replication / Errors / Recommendations sections with
     humanized numbers and inline anomaly highlighting.
   - WRONG_PASSWORD / TIMEOUT_EXCEEDED / MEMORY_LIMIT_EXCEEDED
     entries now carry an inline operator hint pointing at the
     most common local cause.
 .
 Engine + RCA:
   - Canonical context-switch rate from /proc/stat ctxt.
   - cgroup tree walk suppressed only at guard level 2+.
   - "CPU Throttle Cascade" pattern gated on actual
     cpu.cgroup.throttle evidence; new "CPU Oversubscription"
     pattern for hot run-queue without cgroup throttle.
   - Run-queue impact estimate switched to Load1.
 .
 UI:
   - boxRow truncates styled content so the frame never breaks.
   - Duplicate header banner removed from Overview.
   - "Deep metrics paused" notice collapsed to one line with
     R-key to override the resource guard.
   - App Load Distribution falls back to global app instances.
